oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mac McAnally at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Country Music Hall of Fame & Museum (Nashville, Tenn.); McAnally, Mac; Woodcuts (prints);
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Two color window card (black and gold on white) announcing the Nashville Cats series with Mac McAnally at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on September 9. Poster features a woodcut of a car. Mac McAnally is the guitarist, producer and songwriter for Jimmy Buffett, Kenny Chesney, Nanci Griffith, George Jones, George Strait, Keith Whitley and Trisha Yearwood.
